The paper proposes a random CSP model and analyzes the behavior of backtracking algorithm on it. This falls under the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as CSP is a well-known problem in AI. The analysis of the algorithm involves the study of search trees, which is a common topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the nature of hard instances and evaluating the performance of CSP algorithms, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents asymptotic estimates and investigates the behavior of the average number of nodes, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
